<br>
If you're trying to measure damage taken per second, which seems to be the most accurate number to measure, Yelinak isn't the best because of his knockback.  Vindicator would be good but he's a pain to pull and his guards respawn every 30 mins.  If you could arrange to kill him 5 or 10 times and MT every time with controlled AC that would be a great test, but you'ld have to have the cooperation of a fair number of people every day for a week or so.  Velketor is up a lot, not sure what the respawn is on his gaurds but he's also be a pain I think.  Yelinak is certainly convenient, if you can find him up for a night.  I can't think of any bad-ass melee-only rooted mobs. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6629>Brutul Vilesilencer</a><br>

