<br>
I have heard unsubstantiated rumors that AC is capped unbuffed.  In that AC spells/songs will always perform an actual increase in mitigation over unbuffed AC.<br>
<br>
I would like to see a mob tanked at 1200 unbuffed, 1400 unbuffed, then same gear as 1400 but with full AC buffs (bof or aego, CoE, shissar, bard song).<br>
<br>
I am guessing that 1200-1400 is no increase, but that 1400 + AC buffs is an increase in mitigation.<br>
<br>
Also, like the others stated. I wouldnt worry about DPS. Just figure out the average hit (take out kicks bashs misses blocks dodges ripostes parrys etc) from hits actually landed and that will tell you if the AC is mitigating anything.<br>
<br>
You can also look at percentage of attacks missed, however I have heard pretty good data that AC doesnt affect miss rate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uzbik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zbik</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/02 10:24:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm going to test the 1200ac cap Help me develop a plan.</span><hr size=1> yeli tosses you,couldnt get accurate tests on him imo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaerildroigheann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 295<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/02 11:55:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm going to test the 1200ac cap Help me develop a plan.</span><hr size=1> The people who keep talking about damage per second are really missing the point of the tests.  <br>
<br>
The ONLY thing we are testing is mitigation, NOT avoidance.  That is why we're keeping AGI constant.  You can't test two things at the same time anyway.  Even if AC does have an avoidance part separate from AGI (which I don't believe it does), it will be far less valuable when compared to mitigation effects.<br>
<br>
Testing ADPH with a constant AGI totally negates any avoidance and lets you see the full mitigation effects of differing AC values.<br>
<br>
If you were testing avoidance, all you'd do is get a bunch of logs and see how many times he misses you vs. how many times he hits you.  That doesn't really give you any helpful information, does it?<br>
<br>
ADPH, not DPS <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45589">Aeryl Firebrand</a>, Warlord<br>
<a href="http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=4080">Aeril Droigheann</a>, 59 Preserver, Semi-Retired<br>
