</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukryai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kryai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/02 12:07:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm going to test the 1200ac cap Help me develop a plan.</span><hr size=1> you will not be able to conduct a valid test on an uber mob unless it is very strictly done. I.E. only you are attacking, mob stays in the same position and you have clerics chain healing you for ~ 30 minutes. Any other way there really is too many variables to really give your test much accuracy. Perhaps you can do tests like on Lord Koi, Lady Mirenilla, Aaryonar, Jorlleag. Our clerics do not run out of mana while fighting these guys. But you will have to make sure the mob is slowed entire time and start your test after it is slowed. Either way you still need the the force to get there and conduct the test. This would be a great test to do, though it is quite unfeasible. <p>Kryai Soulcarver 
