Druzzil Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utenakha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenakha</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/con's RED</span><br>  Posts: 316<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/02 12:23:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm going to test the 1200ac cap Help me develop a plan.</span><hr size=1> Who cares if yelinak tosses you.  That doesn't matter if you test hit % and average damage per hit (ignoring claws).  If you get tossed out of range he's not attacking, when you are in range he is attacking.  That is part of why you want to test hit % and average dmg per hit and not test dps.  Damage per sec depends on a more factors that are harder to control and hence, its a very poor test criteria.<br>
<br>
Adex, you really can't have multiple people test because you just don't know what they aren't telling you and those things influence the results.  I did all my testing with the same buffs on, exactly the same buffs.  Its really just too much to control to have multiple people all go test with exactly the same set of buffs for large chunks of time, etc.  And by not rigorously controlling those things your test results will be flawed.  If you are insistant on it then use this as your test subjects:<br>
level 60 warrior, maxed defensive skill, shaman agility buff plus primal avatar.  Agi has to be 255.  Use these buffs:<br>
agility, primal avatar (spell NOT proc), aego, focus (single not group on both).  Absolutely NO other buffs and NO fewer buffs.  Turn on all your chat text and let yelinak beat on you for 10+ minutes.  You can't use any parse programs you have to parse it yourself as they won't do what we want...excel will work fine.  Remove all the claw attacks and calculate how many times yelinak hit you and how many he missed.  Calculate the average damage per hit (and if you graph his damage you will see an interesting pattern btw).  Repeat with 50 ac increments from 1100 to 1550 ac by varying armor only keeping all the above factors constant.  That's what I did. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7197 style="text-decoration: none">Gorlab</a> 60 Warlord<BR>
Tenakha 53 Druid<BR>
Officer of <a href=http://www.keepersofthefaith.org style="text-decoration: none">Keepers Of The Faith</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uadexxeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adex Xeda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Swift</BR>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 355<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/02 4:59:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1011.topic&index=39>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I'm going to test the 1200ac cap Help me develop a plan.</span><hr size=1> What do buffs do for you other than to adjust your AC, HP, an agil?<br>
<br>
As long as others are lvl 60 with maxed skills, and are giving me those three numbers that's all I need to start plotting datapoints on my surface plot.<br>
<br>
Plus you don't need everything to be absolutely perfect. All you need is enough data that you can determine a trend or tendancy. We're not building a spaceship with this data.<br>
<br>
My point is, if we can find a flattening slope past a certain (1200?) AC point, we can finally feel comfortable with HP vs. AC decisions.<br>
